definition.value: A steroid sulfate that is 17alpha-hydroxypregnenolone in which the hydroxy hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a sulfo group.
A 18-hydroxy steroid that is cortisol carrying a hydroxy group at position 18. Its urinary excretion is increased in patients with aldosterone-producing adenoma.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of D- and L-o-tyrosine.

A member of the class of 1,4-thiazines that is 3,6-dihydro-2H-1,4-thiazine substituted by carboxy groups at positions 3 and 5. It is a natural but non-proteogenic amino acid found in human urine and brain.
A dialkyl ketone that is heptane in which the two methylene protons at position 4 have been replaced by an oxo group.
A member of the class of naphthoquinones that is 2-methyl-1,4-naphthoquinone which is substituted at position 3 by a (2E)-5-carboxy-3-methylpent-2-en-1-yl group. A urinary metabolite of vitamin K1.
